{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.0.5"}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## The goal of this project was to analyze how what kinds of industries data analysts work in, the technologies they use in these industries, and what the most popular types of data analyst jobs are between data scientists, data analysts, data engineers, and MLE (machine learning engineers).","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"library(ggplot2)\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(dplyr)\n\n\n#We start by loading in our initial data, and the removing any unnecessary collumns of data we will not need\nskills_job_data <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/data-science-job-posting-on-glassdoor/Cleaned_DS_Jobs.csv\")\ncolnames(skills_job_data)\n\nclean_skills_job_data <- skills_job_data %>%\n  select(-one_of(\"Company Name\",\"same_state\",\"Type of ownership\",\"min_salary\", \"same_state\", \"Salary Estimate\",\"Location\", \"max_salary\",\"company_age\",\"Job Description\", \"Headquarters\",\"avg_salary\",\"Rating\",\"Size\",\"Revenue\",\"job_state\",\"seniority\"))\nhead(clean_skills_job_data)\n\n#We rwite out this cleaned data to a new csv file\nwrite.csv(clean_skills_job_data, \"clean_skills_job_data.csv\")","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-03-21T18:19:53.448653Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-03-21T18:19:53.450181Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-03-21T18:19:54.958669Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Here we can see a tible showcasing the necesarry sections of data we will use to perform our analysis.\n\nHowever the data isn't completely usable. The various technologies; python, excel, hadoop, spark, aws, and tableau are represented to be used in certain jobs as 1 and 0, with 1 meaning that it is used and 0 menaing that it isn't. In order to make it easier to count and visualize our data later on, this sheet is then exported as a new csv and the cells for each technology are replaced with their names instead of the binary values.\n\nEx: In the collumn for python all the 1s are replaced with \"python\" and the 0s are left as blank spots.\n\nThe section \"job_simp\" is also renamed to \"job type\" for ease of understanding.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"final_data <- read_csv(\"/kaggle/input/clean-skills-job-data-ver2/clean_skills_job_data_ver2.csv\")\nhead(final_data)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-03-21T18:20:00.967784Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-03-21T18:20:00.969614Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-03-21T18:20:01.132731Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Data Analysis across Industries & Sectors\n## These are the amount of data analysis jobs in various industries.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"final_data %>%\n  drop_na(Industry) %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Industry))) +\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n        text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +\n  labs(y=\"Use of Data Analysis \\nin these Industries\", title = \"Use of Data Analysis Across Industries\",x=\"Industry\") +\n  geom_bar()\n\nfinal_data %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry)) + \n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1), \n        text = element_text(size = 17), \n        plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)) +\n  labs(y=\"Industries in this Sector\", title = \"Sectors by Industry\", x=\"Sector\")+\n  geom_bar()\n\noptions(repr.plot.width = 30)\noptions(repr.plot.height = 30)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-03-21T18:23:33.925393Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-03-21T18:23:33.926980Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-03-21T18:23:36.294432Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Here we can see that data anlysis jobs are most common in the IT Services industry, however many jobs which relate the business Sector also rely heavily on the use of data analysis. As it is the second largest bar in our Sectors by Industry graph.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of Technologies Aceoss Industries\n\n## Now we can take a look at which Industries use which Technologies the most out of Python, Excel, AWS, Hadoop, Saprk, and Tableau","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of Excel Across Industries","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"industry_filter_excel <- filter(final_data, excel == 'excel')\n\nindustry_filter_excel %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry ))+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n       text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+\n  labs(y=\"Industries Using Excel\", x =\"Sector\", title = \"Usage of Excel\") +\n  geom_bar()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T19:31:24.994075Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T19:31:24.995676Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T19:31:25.877588Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of Python Across Industries","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"industry_filter_python <- filter(final_data, python == 'python')\n\nindustry_filter_python %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry ))+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n       text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+\n  labs(y=\"Industries Using Python\", x =\"Sector\", title = \"Usage of Python\") +\n  geom_bar()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T19:31:25.880356Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T19:31:25.881772Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T19:31:26.930495Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of AWS Across Industries","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"industry_filter_aws <- filter(final_data, aws == 'aws')\n\nindustry_filter_aws %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry ))+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n       text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+\n  labs(y=\"Industries Using AWS\", x =\"Sector\", title = \"Usage of AWS\") +\n  geom_bar()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T19:31:26.932332Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T19:31:26.933380Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T19:31:27.588542Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of Hadoop Across Industries","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"industry_filter_hadoop <- filter(final_data, hadoop == 'hadoop')\n\nindustry_filter_hadoop %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry))+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n       text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+\n  labs(y=\"Industries Using Hadoop\", x =\"Sector\", title = \"Usage of Hadoop\") +\n  geom_bar()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T19:31:27.590398Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T19:31:27.591382Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T19:31:28.370368Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of Spark Across Industries","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"industry_filter_spark <- filter(final_data, spark == 'spark')\n\nindustry_filter_spark %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry))+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n       text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+\n  labs(y=\"Industries Using Spark\", x =\"Sector\", title = \"Usage of Spark\") +\n  geom_bar()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T19:31:28.372235Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T19:31:28.373299Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T19:31:29.039998Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Use of Tableau Across Industries","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"industry_filter_tableau <- filter(final_data, tableau == 'tableau')\n\nindustry_filter_tableau %>%\n  ggplot(aes(x=fct_infreq(Sector), fill = Industry))+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 70, hjust=1),\n       text = element_text(size = 20),\n       plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+\n  labs(y=\"Industries Using Tableau\", x =\"Sector\", title = \"Usage of Tableau\") +\n  geom_bar()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T19:35:35.875942Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T19:35:35.877075Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T19:35:36.497565Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"When comparing these charts Information Technology relys primarily on the use of Python, Excel, Spark and AWS. This shows that for many data analysts the information technology sector is best fiit for their abilities if they primarily specialize in those technologies. Furthermore if a data analyist wants to work in the information technology sectore those would be good technologies to invest their time in.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Here we can see what the percentage of the industry uses certain technologies","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"only_technologies <- final_data %>%\n  select(one_of(\"python\",'excel',\"spark\",\"hadoop\",\"aws\",'tableau'))\nonly_technologies_new <- data.frame(unlist(only_technologies))\n\n\ncolnames(only_technologies_new) <- c('Technologies')\nonly_technologies_new <- drop_na(only_technologies_new)\n\n\ncount<-table(only_technologies_new$Technologies)\npercent <-table(only_technologies_new$Technologies)/576\npercent <- round(percent*100)\npie(percent, labels = paste0(percent, \"%\"), col = rainbow(6), main=\"Percentage of Technologies Used \\nby Data Analysts\",cex=2)\nlegend(\"topleft\", legend = c(\"AWS\", \"Excel\", \"Hadoop\", \"Python\", \"Spark\", \"Tableau\"),\n       fill =  rainbow(6))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2022-12-29T22:51:49.900202Z","iopub.execute_input":"2022-12-29T22:51:49.901489Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-12-29T22:51:50.061693Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}